-- Bank of Japan's Miyao Says Stronger Yen May Affect Economy, Asahi Reports
-- Tak Kumakura
-- 2010-08-03T01:23:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-08-03/bank-of-japan-s-miyao-says-stronger-yen-may-affect-economy-asahi-reports.html

          
          
             Bank of Japan board member Ryuzo
Miyao said sustained yen gains may affect the central bank’s
economic outlook, the Asahi newspaper reported. Miyao told the
newspaper in an interview that he will monitor the situation.  
 Asked if the bank plans to ease its monetary stance, Miyao
said any action would depend on whether the yen’s strength hurts
the Japanese economy.  
          
          


  


        